<br>
First, I don't agree with the thought that you should not be making suggestions to bards.  Our MT also happens to be our raid leader.  He generally has a lot more info about particular fights than most of the rest of the guild, he may have a theory he wants to try out, whatever.  If the bard can not take advice, suggestions, etc, that is when you might want to look at finding a new bard.  Bards know their songs a hell of a lot better than you, but you might know the fight better than them.  Work together on it.  Talk about it.  Then pick the song lineup to fit.<br>
<br>
Just to clear up a possible misconception.  There are two main lines of Damage Shield songs....Psalms, and Haste/attack line (Rondo, Warsong, etc.).  You can only have one of each up at a time.....there is no additional bard DS song stacking.  Also, which I am guessing 99% of the people here know, Bard stacking code was rewritten so that bards cannot stack DS's off of items (or Tash, or HP buffs, etc.).  But we can still get you up in that 160+ DS range with Mage DS and potions.<br>
<br>
Added info you may not know about the popular (at least here) Rizlona's Call of Flame.  Not only do you get the benefit of the 30% stackable haste, but you also get the benefit of the 15% added DD damage on DD weapon procs....including lifetaps.  Just another reason to like this song.<br>
<br>
