<br>
Wyndaria, there's some real value to soliciting opinions from the main tanks.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>#1</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I know more about what my songs do, but the tank knows more about what he needs.  Does he want more DPS, even if it sacrifices agro (Psalm of Veeshan + Amp)?  Does he want more agro, even it it sacrifices DPS (Katta's)?  Does he need more damage mitigation (Niv's Harmonic)?<br>
<br>
Which is worth more, an extra 12 DS or 35% stackable haste?<br>
<br>
Once the main tank explains his priorities, then I can determine how (or even if) I best accommodate them, looking at the larger picture of the raid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>#2</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> By listening to these responses, I get a general picture of how well the tanks understand bards.  A lot of these warriors make the exact same selection I would under most circumstances.  That's a good sign.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>#3</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Even though it's phrased as a question, this discussion does help advertise bard abilities.  One warrior mentions that his DS parsed at 205 DPS.  20 other warriors perk up their ears and go <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;It did?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>#4</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The main tank can back you up when you want to switch groups.  Last night I was in a group where I couldn't have much effect, so I shot the main tank a tell: <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Do you want me in your group for DS?&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  One minute later I was in his group.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------<br>
